ğŸ”¹ What Kubernetes Does:
Once you have many containers running (using Docker or other runtimes), Kubernetes helps to:
Deploy containers to multiple servers
Scale them up/down automatically
Load balance traffic between them
Restart crashed containers
Roll out updates safely

Manage networking, storage, secrets, and configs

ğŸ”¹ Core Components:
Component     	Purpose
Pod	           Smallest deployable unit â€” one or more containers
Node	          Physical/virtual machine running pods
Cluster      	 Collection of nodes managed by Kubernetes
Deployment	    Defines how many pods to run and update strategy
Service.      	Exposes pods to network/load balancing
Ingress.      	Manages external access (HTTP/HTTPS)
kubectl	Command-line tool to interact with cluster

