âš™ï¸ How They Work Together
Docker and Kubernetes are complementary, not competitors:

You use Docker to build and package applications into containers.

You use Kubernetes to run, schedule, and manage those containers across many machines.

Example Workflow:
Developer writes code â†’ creates Dockerfile

Build image â†’ push to Docker Hub (registry)

Kubernetes pulls the image â†’ creates pods â†’ runs them on cluster nodes

